Quiz 1

1. In the Java programming language, all source code is first written in plain text files ending with the ______ extension.
a..javac
b..java
c..class
d..txt

 Answer: ____b__

2. The Java compiler generates
a.machine code
b.source code
c.byte code
d.HTML

Answer: __c____

 3. JVM stands for
a.Java Variable Machine
b.Java Variable Method
c.Java Virtual Method
d.Java Virtual Machine
 
 Answer: __d____

4. Write a Java program to print the sum of two numbers.
 
Answer:

 class SumProgram
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
{
	int x=10;
	int y=5;
	int sum;
	
	sum = x+y;
	System.out.println(sum);
    }
}


5. Write the signature of the main method.
  
Answer: ___public static void main(String[] args)___

6. These characters mark the beginning of a single-line comment.
a.//
b./*
c.*/
d./**
Answer: ___a___

 
